The Product Catalog System is a Spring Boot web application that allows users to add and view products.

My Project Structure looks like:

product-catalog - src - main - java/com/example/productcatalog/controller/ProductController.java
                                                
product-catalog - src - main - java/com/example/productcatalog/entity/Product.java  
                                                               
product-catalog - src - main - java/com/example/productcatalog/repository/ProductRepository.java
                                              
product-catalog - src - main - java/com/example/productcatalog/service/ProductService.java
                                              
product-catalog - src - main - java/com/example/productcatalog/ProductCatalogApplication.java

product-catalog - src - resources/

product-catalog - src - main - templates/addProduct.html

product-catalog - src - main - templates/displayProducts.html

product-catalog - src - main - templates/home.html

product-catalog - src - main - static/css/style.css

product-catalog - src - main - application.properties

product-catalog - pom.xml



Maven dependency has been used and the project metadata is as below:- 
Group name :- com.productcatalog 
Artifact:- product-catalog  
Name:- product-catalog 
Description:- Demo project for Spring Boot and Packaging is jar 
Dependencies :- Spring Web, Spring data JPA, MySQL Driver, Thymeleaf

Once I run my application in Intellij, then I will open the browser give http://localhost:8080/products/add to add the name of the product and the price of the product and the category of the product.

Add Product
Name: colgate
Price: 60
Category: Toothpaste
Add Product

And once I click on add it will display the product list as below

Product List

ID	Name	      Price	   Category
1	  Aqualogica	2000.0	 Skin and Hair
2	  colgate	    60.0	   Toothpaste


